      { q: "How would you implement URL preview (show destination before redirect)?", a: "Add a `+` suffix convention (bit.ly does this) or a dedicated `/preview/{code}` route that looks up the destination URL from the same key-value store used for redirect, but instead of a 301/302 renders an interstitial HTML page showing the destination domain, a screenshot thumbnail, and click-through confirmation. Pre-generate and cache the page screenshot asynchronously at creation time using a headless-Chrome render farm (Puppeteer workers pulling from a queue), storing the thumbnail in S3 + CDN so preview pages load in under 200ms without rendering on-demand. Cache the preview HTML itself in Redis/CDN edge (TTL 24h) since destination metadata rarely changes, and invalidate the cache if the fraud-scoring job later flags the URL." }
