        solution: "Consistent hashing ring: each node owns a token range. Key hashed to ring position, owned by 3 clockwise nodes (replication factor=3). Any node can be coordinator (no single coordinator). Quorum: W=2 for writes (2 of 3 replicas must ack). R=2 for reads (read from 2 of 3, return latest version). W+R > N guarantees at least one replica has latest write. Sloppy quorum: if a replica is down, write to next available node (hinted handoff), replay when node recovers.",
