        solution: "Cassandra schema: PRIMARY KEY (channel_id, message_id DESC). channel_id = partition key → all channel messages in one partition. Snowflake ID as message_id: 41-bit timestamp (ms) + 10-bit worker + 12-bit seq. Naturally sortable DESC = newest first. Pagination: SELECT * FROM messages WHERE channel_id = ? AND message_id < last_seen LIMIT 50. Single partition query = very fast. Large partitions: channel with 10B messages = one huge partition (Cassandra 2GB limit). Solution: time-bucket partition: (channel_id, bucket, message_id) where bucket = year+month. On time-range queries, calculate bucket range.",
