        solution: "Content-defined chunking (CDC): split file into variable-size chunks (avg 4MB) using rolling hash (Rabin fingerprinting). Chunk boundaries are determined by content (not fixed offsets), so inserting text doesn't invalidate all subsequent chunks. For each chunk: compute SHA-256. Check Dedup Index: if hash exists, block is already in S3 — no upload needed. Only upload new/changed chunks. Send new file metadata with list of block_ids. Server reconstructs file from blocks. Cross-user dedup: if 10K users have same 4MB chunk, store once (e.g., common image, installer package). ~30% storage savings globally.",
